        Notes for DHCPD.

Purpose: DHCP implements Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol, RFC???

         Overview of source code / files
Headers:
 dhcp.h - Protocol structures.
 dhcpd.h - All Major pointers to data structures used in dhcpd(8), and method declarations for other source files.
 dhctoken.h - Tokens for config file lexer and parser.
 sync.h - dhcpd(8) synchronisation protocol, designed for real-time synchronisation between multiple machnies running the same config.
 tree.h - Definitions for address trees

Source:
 dhcpd.c - Main method







Questions:
 + How will the sync protocol interact with reloading configuration files?
